1. Interface vs Abstract Class?
Answer:
Interface defines only behavior (fully abstract) Abstract class provides both behavior and implementation
A class can implement multiple interfaces but extend only one abstract class
Interfaces are used for loose coupling, abstract classes for shared base logic
 

2. Can we create an object of an interface?
Answer:
No, we cannot create an object of an interface directly.
But we can:
Use reference variable Create object using implementation class
